Overview

This assignment is a practical, hands-on project for groups of five students worth 30% of your final grade. The objective is to find a real-world client with a problem that can be addressed through computer science solutions. This project is divided into three phases: 

Phase 1: Group formation, Collaboration setup, Client engagement and problem identification
Phase 2: Problem description and Solution design
Phase 3: Analysis of the design and final report + Individual reflection

Note 1: Make sure you communicate with your group. All official communication will be on D2L or Google docs. You are welcome to use other tools for unofficial communication. 

Note 2: All group assessments are subject to individual negative marking based on feedback from your group and TA assessment of your contributions.


Phase 1: Group formation, Collaboration setup (3%), Client Engagement and Problem Identification (2%)
